text: Nambour Crushers Rugby League Football Club is an Australian rugby league football club based in Nambour, Queensland formed in 1955. The club was established when two Nambour local teams merge; South Magpies and the All Whites. ==Notable Juniors== *Ray Higgs (1975-78 Parramatta Eels & Manly Sea Eagles) *Ben Ross (2002-13 St George Illawarra Dragons, Penrith Panthers, Cronulla Sharks & South Sydney Rabbitohs) *Joe Boyce (2015- Brisbane Broncos) ==References== ==External links == * Official website Category:Sport in the Sunshine Coast, Queensland Category:Rugby league teams in Queensland Category:Rugby clubs established in 1968 Category:1968 establishments in Australia
